    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nA huge amout of output to the stdout causes coruption of the ui.\nI've checked if there are control characters in the output (script/file) - everything is fine. Maybe an buf overflow?\n\nThe issue only appears when a huge amount of data is written to stdout - For example run a script multiple times, or `cat` a large file multiple times.\n\nSame behavior in the nvim terminal on allacritty and kde konsole. No term-multiplexer involved. On a native terminal there are no issues\n\n<img width=\"2520\" height=\"101\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/44bec492-0157-4e56-83bf-55709e583707\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```bash\nwget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/uBlockOrigin/uAssetsCDN/refs/heads/main/filters/filters.min.txt\n\nvim -u /dev/null\n:te \n\nfor i in `seq 1 100`; do cat filters.min.txt ; done\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nno defects on the ui\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-458+g27909a193d\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux aarch64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nallacritty, kde konsole\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty and xterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nsrc build",
